According to the documentation for method [setBackground][1] (in class `javax.swing.JComponent`):
&gt; It is up to the look and feel to honor this property, some may choose to ignore it.

So it looks like `com.sun.java.swing.plaf.windows.WindowsLookAndFeel` does ignore the *background* property.

One option would be to create a custom [look-and-feel][2].

Another option would be to use `com.sun.java.swing.plaf.windows.WindowsClassicLookAndFeel`.

