One interesting point is that `readUnshared()` will not maintain a reference in the first place, whereas the reset will be performed on the reading side when encountering the reset marker on the next read operation, so the garbage collection is one object behind, compared to the `readUnshared()` approach. Further, as predicted, the serialized data is much bigger when using `reset()`.

